<title>SWEDEN: SWIMMING-POLL BREAKS WOMEN'S 400 FREESTYLE WORLD RECORD.</title>
<headline>SWIMMING-POLL BREAKS WOMEN'S 400 FREESTYLE WORLD RECORD.</headline>
<dateline>GOTHENBURG, Sweden 1997-04-19</dateline>
<text>
<p>Claudia Poll of Costa Rica broke the world women's 400 metres freestyle short-course record on Saturday when she clocked four minutes 00.03 seconds at the world short-course championships.</p>
<p>East German Astrid Strauss set the previous mark of 4:02.05 in Bonn on February 8, 1987.</p>
